Commentary Text: Bhuvneshwar to Roy, out Caught by Dhawan!! Dhawan has claimed a catch. Roy isn't going anywhere. The third umpire will have a look, the soft call is OUT. He has caught it cleanly, but has the ball touched the ground or did Dhawan get his fingers underneath it? The zoomer has been called for, it looks tricky, but the soft signal is OUT. If there's no conclusive evidence, it will stay with the on-field call. The third umpire is taking numerous looks at it. B2$ is the call. GL have lost two of their overseas batting stars now. Coming to the ball, it was banged short and just outside off, Roy was rocking back on the pull, went low of the bat and looped towards mid-wicket. The ball was dying in front of him, but Dhawan does well to dive forward and holds onto it. Roy c Dhawan b Bhuvneshwar 31(21) [4s-5]
